values:
i decided to start updating this thing again. maybe this time i'll actually stick with it instead of doing so for about a week then forget about it/get too lazy.
anyways, i'm pretty stoked because i'm FINALLY getting close to getting back up to 3/4s again :) even though i guess i never really was.. only for aboout a day in one ear before it ripped but ANYWHO. my left ear went right back up to 5/8ths but as for the left, stretching scar tissue is difficult and painful. but it's up to 00 now soo as soon as i get that one caught up and at 5/8th, ill put the 3/4 in. mmmmm i've waited soo long to wear my sexy white tunnels. :p

i'm really loving having two weeks off from school. i hate gene fucking juarez, i can't wait to graduate that damn place. bradley came over today and told me they implemented a couple more bullshit rules; ie. can't have your purse in class anymore or you get written up? the fuck. 
it's bad enough one of the biggest cunts at the school is gonna be my teacher when i come back, i don't wanna deal with anymore stupid shit than i have to. ugggh whyyyyyy didn'tttttttt iiiiiiiiiiiii go tooooo AVEDA!

and in other news, i really want a ferret.

i need to get away. sometimes i want to forever. after i take my trip to portland, if i like it  i'm highly considering moving down there after i finish school. i LOVVVE seattle, and it breaks my heart to think about not calling it home, but i'm so tired of all the assholes that live here, and i feel like all my relationships with people here are falling apart. i'm trying to keep them together but i'm not feeling any effort on the other end. even though some of them i'd rather have over. i've realized there's people i never should have trusted, or considered my friend. but that aside, moving would give me a fresh start and a new atmosphere and just forget about all the stress that's accumulated inside my head in seattle. i've heard portland is a lot like seattle so i shouldn't get too homesick.  :) i'm excited to go there.





look quite a bit alike, yeah?

i'm starting up using livejournal again. i was posting a blog on myspace today and i realized how much i miss keeping a journal. today was pretty lame. as the last few days have been without being able to use my car >:(. i have been enjoying my lazy, relaxing mornings. waking up at noon and then going outside for coffee and cigarettes. 







and i GUESS i like the money i have saved on gas since i haven't been driving around all over the place.. but i'd much rather have my car back. fuck.
